Vladimir Putin said on Wednesday trust had eroded between the United States and Russia under President Donald Trump. WASHINGTON United States (US) President Donald Trump said on Thursday &quot;things will work out fine&quot; between the United States and Russia, a day after he said US-Russian relations may be at an all-time low.&quot;Things will work out fine between the USA and Russia. At the right time everyone will come to their senses &amp; there will be lasting peace!&quot; Trump said in a note on Twitter.Vladimir Putin said on Wednesday trust had eroded between the United States and Russia under President Donald Trump, as Moscow delivered an unusually hostile reception to Secretary of State Rex Tillerson in a face-off over Syria.